MBC+ Drama is joint venture between OSN and MBC Group. It is a 24-hour Arabic channel that offers a range of Arabic drama and Turkish series "First on TV" to OSN subscribers starting February 1, 2009.
MBC+ Drama claims to offer programs up to 3 months before any other channel. MBC+ Drama is the only channel amongst its sister channels at MBC Group that requires subscription.
Not to be confused with MBC Drama, an alternative free-to-air channel, launched on November 27, 2010.
On January 1, 2016, MBC + Drama HD stopped broadcasting replaced with OSN Ya Hala! Cinema HD Promo due to MBC focusing on alternative free-to-air channel MBC Drama and Paid On-Demand Service Shahid PLUS.


